{"type":"message","id":"aa2392ed","parentId":"81749420","timestamp":"2026-03-04T11:30:09.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Devising browser-based model runner plan**\n\nI'm thinking through how to replace the simulated runtime with a real browser-friendly runner using `@xenova/transformers`. The goal is to hook into a lightweight model like 'gpt2', load it dynamically in the browser, and approximate activations and circuit node data from generated tokens since low-level residual hooking may not be supported. I'll plan to create a runtime module that asynchronously loads the pipeline, runs prompts, and derives simplified activation metrics to feed into the UI while handling async state properly. This will involve adding the package, setting up dynamic imports guarded by environment, and designing the `ModelRuntime` interface accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_044be20a9efe26f90169a817a9d13481919db9901c67f379c0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpqBfBoki_CpWAANeRwyDI_ElTZ1RIaFce2bsdIHVpbCxy1FzWeNNRZrhIhy1g_rauawPy5tWxvGW9KZ_URrk-WBdAwQeEf3UdQ22Zm0Ux3gvy184BOjQJ7Pu5897X6ZaisoGUGjSl1_B039EUmqiRYtl_hhTKzvJO-aP35OrVK6Q0Tlc8kpBTVIr-pYke7Uwof6Nuwqcq19IcIsJujcWRF1Zt4pxHrcjEF__q6A2G817u6D1urALVN7itS3mTKS6XjckWfRtrOGDar0BOF2cUSikASpgr6dHvgszS5QA0vC1EKnhwiwqVewgzXamK58LCLm23wQEssmWyS1VdIfZ_HuPZiGK8HqR4ps26D2f4RANBcQLsNSJ8mv61Q9EDJ7B2wTNN5pCFUkqmzqjdIUxOwxf9zvh8gJCR-V5seq7uTaLBO7vpiOtY9cNg1iu59LfBuBxchbAAgw9UJEDcZyA1hLnc2R6mUGWKJvbD4Xp1Q6gaKgnwGEjr2c2Icdi3iY3f7rKLs9n4spa80sBTJ5u26cC8skf6VWICp776WcqgO4dvtxJKvt_zTHWwJwJcAajtQzv0pmBJ4adVomC2N-fXP8cSxzpmEJPpfFqn84TEzqubHMSRSIEGbh_sX_NglV2p7y5qZvPOg3LEX97hoUFRqZV7Osiqt0u_s_SkIzUzVO4hFAtoqRzO3Hb_9Xw7bL2nBkTrhybnlnFhBNybchtvowz7TVXbaB3F9T5zKiZfqB3MeTXRtYp14XvyJUi6YNh87aQbKHqmH-vJnvDXGSxwv6Y21X8Zq-PwW4dYzlQ_VEolrVtsgG4EWMxJB3R2XDYJAJasXCxZyC9hRmSe_vqnd8J7yLy0kUp7JBpZKHnjNLuQvZbVa-KezUaf-Tntil1TaGFXsrY-Q0rhX30p-g5z2UYlCshzIGuZKOD4KadVa7ERBrgwJfysBSGNIzoMoni-83