{"type":"message","id":"f1dd6c3f","parentId":"7fd83ef2","timestamp":"2026-03-04T11:31:32.326Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_v5i441wKPLlX3H4ojSAbpBSA|fc_044be20a9efe26f90169a81813ec388191bed5cf5b6ca00fe9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"6: * Abstract base class for tokenizer models.\n74:     * Loads a pre-trained tokenizer from the given `pretrained_model_name_or_path`.\n76:     * @param {string} pretrained_model_name_or_path The path to the pre-trained tokenizer.\n77:     * @param {PretrainedTokenizerOptions} options Additional options for loading the tokenizer.\n79:     * @throws {Error} Throws an error if the tokenizer.json or tokenizer_config.json files are not found in the `pretrained_model_name_or_path`.\n85:     * @param {Object} tokenizerJSON The JSON of the tokenizer.\n86:     * @param {Object} tokenizerConfig The config of the tokenizer.\n88:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n91:    _tokenizer_config: any;\n93:    pre_tokenizer: PreTokenizer;\n122:     * Returns the value of the first matching key in the tokenizer config object.\n123:     * @param {...string} keys One or more keys to search for in the tokenizer config object.\n131:     * @typedef {Object} BatchEncoding Holds the output of the tokenizer's call function.\n137:     * Encode/tokenize the given text(s).\n138:     * @param {string|string[]} text The text to tokenize.\n172:     * Encodes a single text using the preprocessor pipeline of the tokenizer.\n179:     * Encodes a single text or a pair of texts using the model's tokenizer.\n191:     * Encodes a single text or a pair of texts using the model's tokenizer.\n205:     * Decode a batch of tokenized sequences.\n206:     * @param {number[][]|Tensor} batch List/Tensor of tokenized input sequences.\n243:     * ids. This method is intended for use with chat models, and will read the tokenizer's chat_template attribute to\n254:     * const tokenizer = await AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"Xenova/mistral-tokenizer-v1\");\n262:     * const text = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(chat, { tokenize: false });\n265:     * const input_ids = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(chat, { tokenize: true, return_tensor: false });\n277:     * @param {boolean} [options.tokenize=true] Whether to tokenize the output. If false, the output will be a string.\n278:     * @param {boolean} [options.padding=false] Whether to pad sequences to the maximum length. Has no effect if tokenize is false.\n279:     * @param {boolean} [options.truncation=false] Whether to truncate sequences to the maximum length. Has no effect if tokenize is false.\n280:     * @param {number} [options.max_length=null] Maximum length (in tokens) to use for padding or truncation. Has no effect if tokenize is false.\n281:     * If not specified, the tokenizer's `max_length` attribute will be used as a default.\n282:     * @param {boolean} [options.return_tensor=true] Whether to return the output as a Tensor or an Array. Has no effect if tokenize is false.\n283:     * @param {Object} [options.tokenizer_kwargs={}] Additional options to pass to the tokenizer.\n284:     * @returns {string | Tensor | number[]| number[][]} The tokenized output.\n286:    apply_chat_template(conversation: Message[], { chat_template, add_generation_prompt, tokenize, padding, truncation, max_length, return_tensor, tokenizer_kwargs, ...kwargs }?: {\n289:        tokenize?: boolean;\n294:        tokenizer_kwargs?: any;\n298: * BertTokenizer is a class used to tokenize text for BERT models.\n304: * Albert tokenizer\n328:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n339:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n345:     * @param {string|string[]} raw_inputs The text to tokenize.\n346:     * @param {Object} tokenizer_options Options to be sent to the tokenizer\n350:    _build_translation_inputs(raw_inputs: string | string[], tokenizer_options: any, generate_kwargs: any): any;\n357:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n360:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n385: * The NllbTokenizer class is used to tokenize text for NLLB (\"No Language Left Behind\") models.\n398:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n404:     * @param {string|string[]} raw_inputs The text to tokenize.\n405:     * @param {Object} tokenizer_options Options to be sent to the tokenizer\n409:    _build_translation_inputs(raw_inputs: string | string[], tokenizer_options: any, generate_kwargs: any): any;\n412: * The M2M100Tokenizer class is used to tokenize text for M2M100 (\"Many-to-Many\") models.\n422:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n428:     * @param {string|string[]} raw_inputs The text to tokenize.\n429:     * @param {Object} tokenizer_options Options to be sent to the tokenizer\n433:    _build_translation_inputs(raw_inputs: string | string[], tokenizer_options: any, generate_kwargs: any): any;\n436: * WhisperTokenizer tokenizer\n515:     * // instantiate the tokenizer and set the prefix token to Spanish\n516:     * const tokenizer = await WhisperTokenizer.from_pretrained('Xenova/whisper-tiny');\n517:     * const forced_decoder_ids = tokenizer.get_decoder_prompt_ids({ language: 'spanish' });\n545: * @todo This model is not yet supported by Hugging Face's \"fast\" tokenizers library (https://github.com/huggingface/tokenizers).\n546: * Therefore, this implementation (which is based on fast tokenizers) may produce slightly inaccurate results.\n572:    constructor(tokenizerJSON: any, tokenizerConfig: any);\n577: * Helper class which is used to instantiate pretrained tokenizers with the `from_pretrained` function.\n578: * The chosen tokenizer class is determined by the type specified in the tokenizer config.\n581: * const tokenizer = await AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('Xenova/bert-base-uncased');\n632:     * Instantiate one of the tokenizer classes of the library from a pretrained model.\n634:     * The tokenizer class to instantiate is selected based on the `tokenizer_class` property of the config object\n638:     * - A string, the *model id* of a pretrained tokenizer hosted inside a model repo on huggingface.co.\n641:     * - A path to a *directory* containing tokenizer files, e.g., `./my_model_directory/`.\n642:     * @param {PretrainedTokenizerOptions} options Additional options for loading the tokenizer.\n649: * Additional tokenizer-specific properties.\n653:     * Whether or not the `legacy` behavior of the tokenizer should be used.\n757: * A callable class representing a pre-tokenizer used in tokenization. Subclasses\n758: * should implement the `pre_tokenize_text` method to define the specific pre-tokenization logic.\n766:   * @param {Object} config A configuration object for the pre-tokenizer.\n768:   * @throws {Error} If the provided configuration object does not correspond to any known pre-tokenizer.\n775:     * @param {string} text The text to pre-tokenize.\n777:     * @returns {string[]} The pre-tokenized text.\n780:    pre_tokenize_text(text: string, options?: any): string[];\n783:     * @param {string|string[]} text The text or array of texts to pre-tokenize.\n787:    pre_tokenize(text: string | string[], options?: any): string[];\n789:     * Alias for {@link PreTokenizer#pre_tokenize}.\n790:     * @param {string|string[]} text The text or array of texts to pre-tokenize.\n932://# sourceMappingURL=tokenizers.d.ts.map"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"6: * Abstract base class for tokenizer models.\n74:     * Loads a pre-trained tokenizer from the given `pretrained_model_name_or_path`.\n76:     * @param {string} pretrained_model_name_or_path The path to the pre-trained tokenizer.\n77:     * @param {PretrainedTokenizerOptions} options Additional options for loading the tokenizer.\n79:     * @throws {Error} Throws an error if the tokenizer.json or tokenizer_config.json files are not found in the `pretrained_model_name_or_pa