{"type":"message","id":"b0028aee","parentId":"bda9a5a1","timestamp":"2026-03-04T11:33:34.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Designing model inference and activation extraction**\n\n**Finalizing model runtime integration and error handling**\n\nI’m wrapping up the implementation by refining the model pipeline’s behavior to always fetch logits, building utilities like `getTopIndices`, and ensuring nodes, edges, scrub runs, and patch summaries are generated properly. I’m adding robust loading and error states to the runtime store, updating UI components accordingly, and preparing the new `transformerRunner` module for dynamic import with correct typing and async control. This ensures smooth integration of live activations and graceful fallback handling.\n\n**Designing new transformerRunner module and integration**\n\nI’m mapping out the creation of a new file that dynamically loads and runs the GPT-2 feature-extraction pipeline, processes tokens and logits into activations, nodes, edges, and scrub runs, and returns this structured data with token counts and summaries. The plan includes careful typed array handling, defining React Flow graph elements, enhancing error and loading states in the runtime store, and updating UI components to show the new model status and errors gracefully. This setup will ensure smooth live inference and user feedback.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_044be20a9efe26f90169a81831bb0c819192dae0b34d91493a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpqBiFydKChJJZUhaGawddFINpLpz5aQChx6AX4pNKlFMX6Jw2P2pE4mdTkr4e8MnUBL168UKUHPkxGHW96KRJz8bx0-Gj8Oy-0ZFIz5QElRa_4DtCEnWkF4Rr5WfHN7zQNTYnUHobxfmTnb7sTFyuwfKFzF579sZwsqtUHfWgMqLej99aADAswPho0mi0KIJcf_1XeSVChLe2are1gdZ0oUGKf_NgchmuQ8cbp7r0mUzcz1VsFHhGXqEmA7cd45UVYKgwJZIeCpi7gkErdlii2GnfBxSDal2yULljKKC4H7ULVUd7FMywkhTcQG4d4ZcpxWJ1Hy6XKVmL-xHMfFA2naOEsmVSLdYk8FTbMlMCx_p277o_ylDwUciFY-aClVnnL1uyH_Nwf2l_DyjK4Hify46ps9Z-IqscnQ2YuM1a3gpH2UQrxb9Mv-mfOU8ATt